𝐁𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐏𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐢𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐌𝐥 & 𝐃𝐋 𝐦𝐨𝐝𝐞𝐥𝐬 𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐌𝐢𝐧𝐝𝐦𝐚𝐩 𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐭

1. 𝐈𝐧𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐚𝐥 𝐀𝐧𝐚𝐥𝐲𝐬𝐢𝐬:
👉Review Hypotheses: Analyze dataset, problem formulation, and initial assumptions.
👉Overfitting/Underfitting:
-- Identify model complexity issues.
-- Overfitting: Use more data, regularization, dropout.
-- Underfitting: Increase model complexity, more epochs.
2. 𝐄𝐫𝐫𝐨𝐫 𝐀𝐧𝐚𝐥𝐲𝐬𝐢𝐬:
👉Types of Errors: Use confusion matrix for classification errors (Type 1 and Type 2).
👉 Systematic errors: Check for mislabeling or data imbalance.
3. 𝐎𝐩𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐢𝐳𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐌𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐨𝐝𝐬:
👉Hyperparameter Tuning:
-- Grid Search: Test all parameter combinations.
-- Random Search: Efficient random sampling of hyperparameters.
-- Bayesian Optimization: Probabilistic model for more optimal solutions.
4. 𝐌𝐨𝐝𝐞𝐥 𝐈𝐦𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬:
👉 Baseline Models:
-- Establish strong baseline (e.g., XGBoost for structured data, ResNet for images).
👉Ensemble Learning: Combine multiple models to leverage their strengths.
👉 Custom Loss Functions: Tailor metrics to business needs.
5. 𝐀𝐝𝐯𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞𝐝 𝐓𝐞𝐜𝐡𝐧𝐢𝐪𝐮𝐞𝐬:
👉Transfer Learning: Fine-tune pre-trained models on specific datasets.
👉AutoML: Use automated tools for model selection and optimization.
6. 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚-𝐂𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐜 𝐄𝐧𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬:
👉Data Augmentation: Generate synthetic data to expand datasets.
👉Feature Engineering: Create or select features that enhance model performance.
👉Active Learning: Retrain model based on error-prone predictions.
7. 𝐌𝐨𝐝𝐞𝐥 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐥𝐨𝐲𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭:
👉Collaboration & Deployment: Ensure models meet both technical and business requirements for real-world application.
